{
  "stem": "14251.6",
  "chunk_idx": 9,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 7.9,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "My mother's sister, during the time that Terezin or Theresienstadt, where she first was with her husband and my grandfather, that was a show camp [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] until it became a transit camp and different kinds of people came there then, not just German-speaking.",
      "word_count": 46
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] She had given someone a postcard to mail, which even has a return address with a street in this camp.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And it was addressed to my grandmother's neighbors, the same family I mentioned earlier several times, Baus.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And it said, I wonder how you are.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And I wonder-- haven't heard a long time from [NON-ENGLISH], which was a disguised way of saying my name, like little Evy, and her mother.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And I hate to inform you that father was released from his suffering on May 4-- one day after my mother's birthday-- 1944, [PAUSES FOR 5 SECONDS] yes, a year after he had been put there and that she had received a little package that was sent by them with some foodstuffs and thank you so much.",
      "word_count": 57
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And that was it.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Ruth.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, she, as it turned out-- again, I just found that out in recent years since the Black Books were compiled.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And I again got verifications now.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "The Russians let go of some records.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And the British got better organized with the records at [INAUDIBLE] and so forth.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "She had been-- oh, and then an eyewitness that I found in England, who was also a nurse, same hospital, same age group.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "That was my last stop.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "I had looked for decades for a nurse who might have survived.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And she wrote to me in English and said, yes, I knew your aunt.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "I went to school with her at the hospital.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And I last saw her in Bergen-Belsen.",
      "word_count": 7
    }
  ],
